Hi Jeremy.  I agree signal has a lot to do with it.  It&#39;s so strange here in my office... I have 
worse reception in one area than another when doing manual sweep.  And when I use the 
MiniBox, it&#39;s much better if it turn it on it&#39;s side with the top facing my hallway, rather than 
having it upright facing the ceiling.  

Good luck with the Speakjet box.  That will be cool.  I&#39;m basically an electronics moron.  I 
can use stuff just fine.  I can even hook up multiple items and make them all work together 
like my TV, Satellite Box, DVD burner/player, and the surround sound.  Or my computers 
and various equipment.  But building something, even with instructions, would be a real 
stretch!   ;-)

Margaret

--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, Early Cuyler &lt;ecuyler@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt; I&#39;ve got the 20-125 and an older 12-469 sans speaker and clicking.  The 20-125 works 
wonderfully and has produced great results.  The 12-469 has produced great results also.  
Bruce can testify to the communication he gets with the 20-125.  
&gt; 
&gt; In the end, it all depends on signal strength and our spirit friends capability to 
communicate, not to mention our state of mind when we conduct a session.  There are a 
lot of variables involved, so there really is no one box better than the others in my opinion.  
Although, Frank seems to get some tremendous results with his creations.
&gt; 
&gt; I&#39;m actually going to attempt a Speakjet box.  I hope I can get past my semi-electronic 
retardedness and make it work.  
&gt; 
&gt; Jeremy
